<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3175> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3175" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Verr. 2.4.112; Lael. 37; Att. 13.32.3; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125f., 470f. (P. Popi[11]ius C. f. P. [n. Laenas]; Rupilius' name entire){498} Chr. 354 (Laenas et Calibo); Fast. Hyd. (Laenate et Rutilio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod., with Sulpicius for Rupilius; and on Popillius, CIL 1\n     .2.637; Cic. Cluent. 95. The Consuls had charge of the senatorial inquisition into supporters of Ti. Gracchus (Cic. Lael. 37; Val. Max. 3.7.1). Popillius built and repaired roads in Italy (CIL 1(2).2.637, 638- ILS 23), while Rupilius finally subdued the slave revolt in Sicily (Cic. Verr. 2.3.125; Liv. Per. 59; Diod. 34-35.2.20-23; Val. Max. 2.7.3; 6.9.8; 9.12, ext. 1; Oros. 5.9.7), possibly earning a triumph (Degrassi 558), and with the help of a senatorial commission reorganized the island under the Lex Rupilia (Cic. Verr. 2.2.32-44, 59, 90, 125; Val. Max. 6.9.8; Ps.-Ascon. 264 Stangl; Schol. Gron. 334 Stangl; cf. CIL 1(2), p. 764, no. 383 n, P. Ru[pilius]). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3131> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3131" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date under the Lex Villia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10207> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10207" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ovation? de Sicilia. Itgenshorst no.214b (ovatio incertus), Rich no. 214. Not listed in MRR." .
